external_knowledge:
- 'popular posts' refers to posts that have received more than 10 upvotes; 
- 'a lot of engagement recently' refers to posts with some activity (a post or reply) within the last 30 days; 
- 'high number of replies' is more than 5 on average.

- Being "most active" refers to the users with the most recent activity, as determined by the 'activity_date' column; 
- "Reputable" refers to the users with the highest 'reputation' points; 
- "Active users" refers to users who have at least one post.

sql:
SELECT topic, (vote_up - vote_down) AS net_votes
FROM posts
ORDER BY net_votes DESC, topic ASC;

